// 1-chip analog/cosim event smoke test charge stimulus.
//
// Test intent:
// - after the startup configuration writes have enabled south TX, enabled
//   channel 0, and unmasked channel 0, inject a single charge pulse into the
//   analog/cosim frontend on channel 0
// - the injected charge is chosen to cross the current RTL/model default
//   threshold and generate one natural event packet
//
// Required passing conditions for the paired run script:
// - one charge event on channel 0 is applied after configuration completes
// - the FPGA later receives a downstream data packet corresponding to that hit
{
  "charges": [
    {
      "runtime_id": 0,
      "tick": 600,
      "channel": 0,
      "charge": -5.0e-15
    }
  ]
}
